00:01:05.400 --> 00:01:10.440
BAE Systems envisions a future where lenses
are made with laser beams controlling hot

00:01:10.440 --> 00:01:11.440
air bubbles.

00:01:11.440 --> 00:01:17.230
The Laser Developed Atmospheric Lens system
creates lenses by layering hot air bubbles

00:01:17.230 --> 00:01:21.780
on colder air using laser pulses which then
refract light.

00:01:21.780 --> 00:01:27.170
This concept is similar to how how current,
solid lenses made of plastic or glass work

00:01:27.170 --> 00:01:31.310
but making one out of air would allow it to
be much larger and maneuverable.

00:01:31.310 --> 00:01:36.950
This technique could also be used to deflect
laser attacks by dispersing the beam.

00:01:36.950 --> 00:01:39.940
So basically like laser beam shields in sci
fi movies.

00:01:39.940 --> 00:01:44.260
But this is just a concept for now - no prototypes.

00:01:44.260 --> 00:01:45.390
