00:01:45.390 --> 00:01:50.730
WaveOptics is developing wearable augmented
reality technology to overlay computer graphics

00:01:50.730 --> 00:01:52.240
on the real world.

00:01:52.240 --> 00:01:57.140
Their headset, nicknamed “the ghost” is
designed for developers and not as a consumer

00:01:57.140 --> 00:02:02.280
device, and they say their fully transparent
display creates sharp holograms with a wide

00:02:02.280 --> 00:02:03.400
field of view.

00:02:03.400 --> 00:02:07.979
Their proof of concept videos show how this
could be used in work and leisure scenarios

00:02:07.979 --> 00:02:12.799
- basically getting one step closer to turning
the world into a videogame.

00:02:12.799 --> 00:02:17.709
ICAROS is a fitness flying virtual reality
game controller machine.

00:02:17.709 --> 00:02:22.909
The active VR experience connects wirelessly
to a headset and demands your full body to

00:02:22.909 --> 00:02:25.319
control flying through the game.

00:02:25.319 --> 00:02:30.189
Navigating inside the rings requires shifting
your weight and is more like a futuristic

00:02:30.189 --> 00:02:33.079
exercise device than a gaming peripheral.

