00:04:58.090 --> 00:05:11.630
Sound waves are picked up by this wonderful
mechanical ear, the microphone, which is really

00:05:11.630 --> 00:05:13.860
a glorified telephone transmitter.

00:05:13.860 --> 00:05:20.690
The power from the microphone is amplified
about ten million times by these vacuum tubes,

00:05:20.690 --> 00:05:25.900
making the voice current strong enough to
operate the machine that photographs the sound.

00:05:25.900 --> 00:05:28.040
Do you follow me?

00:05:28.040 --> 00:05:36.060
And then this amplified current, is carried
by wires along through the theater and down

00:05:36.060 --> 00:05:42.310
to the screen on the stage to connect with
the loudspeakers.

00:05:42.310 --> 00:05:49.280
This is a typical layout of the stage set
with two horns behind the screen.

00:05:49.280 --> 00:05:54.440
The receivers connected to the horns convert
the electrical vibrations back into sound

00:05:54.440 --> 00:05:57.570
waves exactly the way the telephone receiver
operates.

00:05:57.570 --> 00:06:03.310
So that while the picture is being shown the
sound, which was recorded, is reproduced in

00:06:03.310 --> 00:06:04.700
step with the picture.

00:06:04.700 --> 00:06:09.340
The screen is full of small holes so that
the horns may be placed behind the screen

00:06:09.340 --> 00:06:11.190
to let the sound through.

00:06:11.190 --> 00:06:15.560
This gives the illusion that the sound is
coming from the image of the speaker.

